SIMPLE: hand-out
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: hand-out
<hw>hand"-out</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>money or an object given in or as in a charitable
gesture; -- also used of government disbursements to individuals for
welfare; <as>as, government <ex>hand-outs</ex> to welfare
clients</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a printed circular distributed gratis, usually for
political or advertising purposes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>a printed statement distributed, usually to the news
media.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>handover</ent>⟦br⟧
